\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. P. daonensis} (Leybold) Leybold,{\i  Flora}({\i Regensb.}){\b  38}: 345 (1855) ({\i P. oenensis} Thomas ex Gremli). Efarinose. Longest leaves 1·5-7 × 0·6-2 cm, narrowly cuneate-obovate, more rarely ovate, dentate towards the apex, fleshy, viscid, covered with glandular hairs; hairs producing a reddish-black or brown secretion, the longest usually 0·15-0·5 mm; shrunken apical cells depressed laterally. Scape 1·5-9 cm, usually longer than the leaves in fruit, 2- to 8-flowered. Bracts 1-6 mm, ovate to transversely ovate, more or less scarious. Pedicels 1-9 mm. Calyx 2·5-6 mm. Corolla pink to lilac, usually white at the throat. Capsule about as long as calyx. 2n = 62, 63, 64.{\i  Rocks and stony alpine pastures; calcifuge. • E. Alps from} 9° 45' {\i to} 11° {\i E.} Au He It.
