\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs; when perennial, often caespitose. Leaves usually basal. Flowers bracteate, borne singly or in umbels; homostylous. Calyx campanulate or subglobose; lobes triangular. Corolla-tube somewhat inflated, usually shorter than calyx; throat constricted, closed by a ring of scales. Filaments very short, without dilated base, not connate. Capsule spherical, dehiscing almost to the base; seeds 2-many.
